message.text:
KANJI Quiz!
Do you know the meaning of the Kanji "怠"？ Choose the answer!
1. group 2. language 3. lazy

[Hint] It is the opposite meaning of "Ganbaru”（頑張る、がんばる）.
In Japan, it has been very humid because of this rainy season which makes us "怠ける"（なまける, Namakeru) easily...It is time for us to push ourselves to prepare for Summer!?
http://www.anime-manga.jp/KanjiGame/School/　
「怠」の意味はどれ？最近は梅雨でじめじめして思わず怠けてしまいます。夏に向けてそろそろ怠けるのをやめて頑張りましょうか？

message.text:
Do you remember what day is Sunday, June15, 2014? 
YES! It's Father's Day （父の日、ちちのひ） in Japan and some countries!
In Japanese, there are various ways to call your father inlcuding "Otosan"（お父さん） "Otochan"（お父ちゃん） "Tosan"（父さん）"Papa"（パパ）"Oyaji"(親父）"Otou"（おとう）etc.. How do you express your gratitude your father on this Father's Day? Happy Father's Day, Otosan in the world!
今週の日曜日は何の日でしょう？そう！「父の日」！皆さん何をプレゼントしますか？世界中のお父さん、いつもありがとう！
http://words.marugotoweb.jp/search_detail.php?id=1249%2C220&p=1&q=父&source=search&lang=en
